Now we show the formal decoding algorithm. As the \subs phase and repair phase are straightforward, we only give the description of \emph{\ttelim}, aiming to solve a $t\times t$ \sxor system. Without loss of generality, we assume that the parity chunks are $\boldsymbol{c}_{1}$, \ldots, $\boldsymbol{c}_{t}$ and data chunks to decode are $\boldsymbol{d}_{1}$, \ldots, $\boldsymbol{d}_{t}$. Let $d$ denote the maximum integer such that $t_{d,2}-t_{d,1}\leq 0$. Initially, $l_1=l_2=1$.
At the beginning, the \ttelim executes the following iterations:
\begin{itemize}
\item For $b=1,2,\ldots, t-d-1$, for each iteration $l_1$ in $[\sum_{p=1}^{b-1}(s_{t-p,p+1}-s_{t-p,p})+1:\sum_{p=1}^{b}(s_{t-p,p+1}-s_{t-p,p})]$, solve $d_{u}[l_1-\sum_{p=1}^{u-1}(s_{t-p,p+1}-s_{t-p,p})]$ sequentially for $u=1,2,\ldots,b$. 
\item For $b=1,2,\ldots, d-1$, for each iteration $l_2$ in $[\sum_{p=1}^{b-1}(s_{p+1,p}-s_{p+1,p+1})+1:\sum_{p=1}^{b}(s_{p+1,p}-s_{p+1,p+1})]$, solve $d_{t-u+1}[l_2-\sum_{p=1}^{u-1}(s_{p+1,p}-s_{p+1,p+1})]$ sequentially for $u=1,2,\ldots,b$.
\end{itemize}
Then the following iterations are executed sequentially.
\begin{itemize}
    \item Solve $d_u[l_1-\sum_{p=1}^{u-1}(s_{t-p,p+1}-s_{t-p,p})]$ sequentially using previously solved bits, for $u=1,2,\ldots,t-d$.
    \item Solve $d_{t-u+1}[l_2-\sum_{p=1}^{u-1}(s_{p+1,p}-s_{p+1,p+1}]$ sequentially using previously solved bits, $u=1,2,\ldots,d$.
\end{itemize}
Note that in the above process, solving one bit implies that it is substituted into the parity chunks it involves in.

